      • topologicalSort

        protected java.util.ArrayList<AIAI.COP> topologicalSort(java.util.ArrayList<Course> list,
                                                        AIAI.CourseTable gCT)
        topologicalSort() sorts the courses of the course as follows: Let the list of Courses passed to this method be a directed acyclic graph with each Course object in that list being a node. Let the prerequisites of each course represesnt edges pointing from the prerequisite to the node with the prerequisite but only if said prerequisite is in the graph. The following algorithm enumerates the number of edges pointing to each node. Then it removes all nodes with no antecedents from the graph. The algorithm repeats until there are no more nodes in the graph.

        Parameters:
        list - The courses to be sorted by order the courses can be taken.
        gCT - A master lookup table of courses.
        Returns:
        The courses each paired with a number indicating ordering.
        See Also:
        AIAI.COP
